The job of an upper control arm is to locate
the axle side to side and prevent any pinion

00:00:45.809 --> 00:00:50.010
angle changes otherwise known as axle rap
or axle windup.

00:00:50.010 --> 00:00:54.780
The factory stuff utilizes some pretty soft
rubber bushings, which are notorious for flexing

00:00:54.780 --> 00:00:59.109
or distorting on hard launches, and aggressive
cornering which can cause a bunch of wheel

00:00:59.109 --> 00:01:01.120
hop, and inconsistent handling.

